UGHELLI – A group, Urhobo Youth Vanguard has called on the Senior Special Assistant to the Governor on Peace Building and Conflict Resolution, Olorogun Gordons Okomitie to contest for the Delta State House of Assembly seat, Ughelli South Constituency, come 2023. The group which made this known in a statement signed by its National President, Comrade Owen Oghenero Edafe stated that their executives spread across Delta Central Senatorial District and they are ready to purchase the PDP expression of interest form for Okomitie. They noted in the statement that their decision to call on Okomitie to run for the Delta State House of Assembly seat was because of his past antecedents and the believe that he will give positive representation if elected. Ekiti Governorship Election: Kolawole Receives Certificate Of… Bye-Election: Alade Olanrewaju Lawson Wins APC Primary The group urged the youths of Ughelli South Local Government Area to join them to prevail on Olorogun Samson Gordons Okomitie to contest the Ughelli South Constituency, House of Assembly seat in the forthcoming 2023 general election. According to the statement, “there is a great need for Okomitie to be elected member House of Assembly, Ughelli South Constituency in 2023 because it is the time for the youths to take over governance. “We want him to go there to make a change for all Urhobo Youths most especially the youths of Ughelli South Local Government Area. We plead with you to accept our plea and answer our call to run”, the statement added.